uninitialized pointer
memory leak
dangling pointer

we can directly assign address value to the pointer 
int *p;
p=(int*)0x5638;

when ever declare a reference it has to be initialized

int x=10;

int &y=x;

now y is pointing to x with x having the address and the same address is set to y

